line_1: Nor seem'd unlike, in this mistaken Rank,
line_2: The sightless Wretch, who froze upon a Bank

line_1: When kings, queens, knaves, are set in decent rank,
line_2: Expos'd in glorious heaps the tempting bank,

line_1: It's no in titles nor in rank;
line_2: It's no in wealth like Lon'on Bank,

line_1: Thou ance was i' the foremost rank,
line_2: A filly buirdly, steeve an' swank,

line_2: An' set weel down a shapely shank,

line_1: Or is thine house, though less superb thy rank,

line_1: Bless'd Pow'rs, and Beings of the highest Rank,
line_2: Nor love the flowing Stream, nor flow'ry Bank.
